  <p>Before Go 1.22, the output would be:
2 3
2 3
2 3
The <code>for range</code> loop uses short variable declaration (<code>:=</code>) to iterate variables. It&rsquo;s important to note that variables <code>i</code> and <code>v</code> are reused in each loop iteration, not re-declared.</p>]]></description>
